Looking for anyone who may have known Cpl. Jerrald (Jerry)<br>
Rich Thompson, USMC, who died in Quang Tin, South Vietnam on June 16,1966. My understanding is that most, if not all of Jerry's platoon was lost. As a young kid, I remember reading an article in the Readers Digest of the battle which cost Jerry his life. I believe it was something like Hill 323.<br>
Jerry was my cousin, and for some reason, after a lot of years, he came into my mind a few days ago, and I have been searching for information on line since. I want to show it to my children, so that they will know what &quot;sacrifice&quot; is about.<br>
If anyone can provide me with information or a site to search, I would be appreciative. I tried the Readers Digest site, but their on line archives don't go back that far.<br>

